cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper presents an automatic method for segmentation of the left ventricle in cardiac CT angiography scans using convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in computer vision.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses machine learning techniques, specifically convolutional neural networks, for segmentation of the left ventricle in cardiac CT angiography scans.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper presents an AI-based method for segmentation of the left ventricle in cardiac CT angiography scans.
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper uses neural networks, specifically convolutional neural networks, for segmentation of the left ventricle in cardiac CT angiography scans.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with segmentation of medical images, which can be considered a form of multimedia.
